9/4/20, 15:44 - Meghana Kulkarni Arka Book Club: Book Name: My Cousin Rachel
Author: Daphne Du Maurier
Genre: Classic, Thriller
Rating: 🌟🌟🌟

The book, “Rebecca” 💃by the same author has left a very high benchmark in my mind for Daphne Du Maurier. Unfortunately, both the books that I read after that, Jamaica Inn and My Cousin Rachel do not come even close to the brilliancy that was Rebecca. To say I was sorely disappointed would be a heavy understatement.😕
*
 📖🔖🔥🌾
*
I love Daphne’s style of writing. The way she brings the whole setting to life is something that I look forward to in all her books. With this regard, she doesn’t disappoint in My Cousin Rachel. The beautiful scenery, the houses, the layout of the rooms, the gardens, even the dismal rainy days… Daphne paints a strikingly clear picture, and takes you right into the English countryside.
*
 📖🔖🔥💖
*
I was not happy with the way the protagonists were painted. I absolutely hated the character of Philip Ashley. He’s shown as an extremely immature guy, with no sense of the world, no intuition about right and wrong, and completely insensitive to the feelings of the people close to him. Rachel, on the other hand, is shown as a shrewd and sensitive woman throughout, however there is a shroud of villainy around her. I liked Philip’s godfather, Nick Kendall and his daughter Louise. Mr. Kendall is an intelligent person, and Louise shows strength of character and a good amount of common sense. Unfortunately, neither have much say in the whole story, as Philip ignores their warnings and advices consistently.
*
 📖🔖🔥🌾
*
The ending of the book was extremely frustrating. Some might like the style the author has adopted to close the book. Not me. I need closure. I need to know who to hate. I need to know the answers to my questions. And I need to shut up now, else I’ll end up giving out a spoiler.
*
📖🔖🔥💖
*
Let me just say: don’t read the book if you don’t like loose ends in a mystery book. If you’re ok with them, definitely go for it, coz Daphne’s writing is something to die for. ❤️❤️

