 For those who don’t have LinkedIn-

Amongst the many goals I setup this year, I excelled at 

READing consistently. 

One of my goals post maternity break was to go back to reading habit—and I’m happy to say, it’s been a success!

In contrast to last year's one-book completion, I’ve read 15 books and close to 3,000 pages so far!

Looking back, three key strategies helped me stay on track:

1️⃣Joining a Reading Challenge with a Great Book Club
Accountability and community made a huge difference in staying consistent.
2️⃣Tracking Weekly Progress (Minimum 10 Pages a Day)
Simple, manageable goals helped me stay motivated and see steady progress.
3️⃣Timing My Reading After My Daughter Sleeps
Prioritizing a specific time each day made it easier to stick with the habit.

This approach aligns closely with the framework James Clear outlines in Atomic Habits:

🕒Small habits compound: Reading just 10 pages a day adds up to 3,650 pages in a year.
🕒Focus on systems and cues: Being part of a book club kept me accountable and tracked my progress.
🕒Identity-based habits: My goal wasn’t just to log pages—it was about growing and improving, which kept me coming back.

In the end, when you love something, you’ll always find the time for it. And when you're rewarded for doing what you love, you’ll stick with it for the long haul.
